Food Banks and Schools

Aryan Safi

2023-05-23

Purpose

The purpose of this file is to visualize the locations of places of interest to Kristin Butcher and Camilo Garcia-Jimeno and plot the trends of visits and visitors over time in the Safegraph Legacy data.

Part 1: Load Libraries, Data, and Store NAICS Codes

# store packages needed for code
packages = c(
  "tidyverse",
  "htmlwidgets",
  "arrow",
  "sf",
  "tinytiger",
  "tigris",
  "collapse",
  "data.table",
  "coefplot",
  "ggthemes",
  "leaflet",
  "here"
)

for (pkg in packages) {
  if (!require(pkg, character.only = TRUE)) {
    install.packages(pkg)
    library(pkg)
  }
}

options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)

# READ IN THE DATA
safegraph_data = read_feather(here("data/raw/food_banks_raw_dta.feather")) %>%
  select(
    placekey,
    parent_placekey,
    location_name,
    naics_code,
    latitude,
    longitude,
    street_address,
    city,
    region,
    postal_code,
    raw_visit_counts,
    raw_visitor_counts,
    date
  )

# turn into data.table
safegraph_data = as.data.table(safegraph_data)

Part 2: Load TIGRIS Shapefiles and Store NAICS Codes

# store the list of non-contiguous US states for filtering
states_to_remove = c(
  "HI",
  "AK",
  "VI",
  "PR",
  "MP",
  "GU",
  "AS"
)

# let's load in the state shape files for the background of the map  
state_shp = tigris::states(year = 2019) %>%
  filter(!STUSPS %in% states_to_remove)

# store the CRS of the state_shp file 
crs_to_match = st_crs(state_shp)

## STORE NAICS CODES FOR FILTERING
food_naics = 624210

# PRIMARY SCHOOLS
primary_naics = 611110

# COLLEGE NAICS
college_naics = 611310

# JUNIOR COLLEGES
juco_naics = 611210

# CHILDCARE NAICS
child_naics = 624410

# OTHER
other_naics = c(
  611519,
  # Technical and Trade Schools
  611610,
  # Fine Arts Schools
  611511,
  # Cosmetology and Barber Schools
  611699,
  # All other Miscellaneous Schools and Instruction (yoga instruction)
  611410,
  # Business and Secretarial Schools
  611692,
  # Automobile Driving Schools
  611630  # Language Schools
  )

Part 3: Food Banks Trends and Map

# filter the data to the food banks naics code
plot_data = safegraph_data[naics_code == food_naics]

# replace missing visits and visitor values to 0
plot_data = plot_data %>%
  mutate(
    raw_visit_counts = ifelse(is.na(raw_visit_counts), 0, raw_visit_counts),
    raw_visitor_counts = ifelse(is.na(raw_visitor_counts), 0, raw_visitor_counts)
  )

# store number of POIs
obs = length(unique(plot_data$placekey))

# store type 
type = "Food Banks"

# plot the distribution of raw visits
ggplot(plot_data) +
  geom_histogram(aes(x = raw_visit_counts),
                 color = 'red',
                 fill = 'red') +
  theme_fivethirtyeight() +
  labs(title = paste0("Distribution of Visits to ", type),
       subtitle = "Safegraph Legacy Data",
       caption = paste0("Number of Observations: ", obs)) +
  guides(color = 'none',
         fill = 'none')

# plot the distribution of raw visitors
ggplot(plot_data) +
  geom_histogram(aes(x = raw_visitor_counts),
                 color = 'light blue',
                 fill = 'light blue') +
  theme_classic() +
  labs(title = paste0("Distribution of Visitors to ", type),
       subtitle = "Safegraph Legacy Data",
       caption = paste0("Number of Observations: ", obs)) +
  guides(color = 'none',
         fill = 'none')

# remove POIs in non-contiguous states
plot_data_contig = plot_data %>%
  filter(!region %in% states_to_remove)

# create point geometries in the safegraph_data using the coordinates
plot_data_contig = plot_data_contig %>%
  st_as_sf(coords = c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = 4326)

# match the safegraph data's CRS to match the state_shp file
plot_data_contig = st_transform(plot_data_contig, crs_to_match)

# next convert the safegraph data to an sf object by creating a point geometry from the coordinates
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = state_shp, color = 'white', fill = 'light gray') +
  geom_sf(data = plot_data_contig, color = 'red') +
  theme_map() +
  labs(title = paste0(type, " in the Contiguous US",
       subtitle = "Safegraph Legacy Data"))

# prepare data
plot_data = plot_data %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(date)) %>%
  fgroup_by(date) %>%
  fsummarise(visits = fsum(raw_visit_counts),
             visitors = fsum(raw_visitor_counts))

# plot visits
ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = visits), color = 'red') +
  labs(
    title = paste0("Visits Over Time to ", type) ,
    subtitle = "Safegraph Legacy Data",
    y = "Visits",
    x = "Week"
  ) +
  theme_pander()

# plot visitors
ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = visitors), color = 'blue') +
  labs(
    title = paste0("Visitors Over Time to ", type) ,
    subtitle = "Safegraph Legacy Data",
    y = "Visitors",
    x = "Week"
  ) +
  theme_pander()
